nodes.text: The CL69 Landspeeder was a landspeeder model produced by Ubrikkian Industries, and was still in existence in the galaxy by the year 0 ABY. The CL69 could travel up to 330 kilometers per hour. A CL69 Landspeeder was used by a Rebel Alliance cell on the planet of Brentaal IV in 0 ABY. It aided a group of Alliance privateers from the frigate Far Orbit, though an Alliance contact died along the way to escape the Galactic Empire's ISB agents, who were following them.

The CL69 Landspeeder first appeared in Raid on Brentaal, an adventure scenario in 1998's The Far Orbit Project, by Timothy S. O'Brien. The book was a supplement to West End Games's Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game and had the same theme of the previous publication Pirates & Privateers, as it followed the privateering vessel Far Orbit.
